Soil respiration. Banana project

Raquel Correa

2023-10-24

Evolution of soil respiration over time

One way to measure the microbial community of a soil is respiration. Check how much CO2 is released from it.

  1. Basal respiration: The falcon tubes (50 ml), with the original soil samples, were placed in jars with hermetic closure. The evaluation of respiration (CO2 production) was carried out by titration of the sodium hydroxide (0.5 M) with hydrochloric acid (0.5 M) once the sample has been incubated for 7 days at 25ºC.

  2. Induced respiration: Induced respiration was carried out once basal respiration had been evaluated (that is, on the same samples). A solution is added of 20% sterile glucose (0.5 ml/sample). Subsequently, the samples were incubated at 25ºC for 2.5 days and the sodium hydroxide (0.5 M) was titrated with hydrochloric acid (0.5 M).
